			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I started swarm kiting recently (AE kiting got dull) and im having some pretty big problems.  I'm lvl 35 and currently in EW doing the walrus'. I go out, grab a bunch of em, charm one and sick it after another.  Then I loop my swarm around to get it on the pet. They start bashing it, I wait and usually charm breaks right after that. Unfortunatly I haven't gotten my timing down yet, so charm breaks with the mob at 30% health sometimes.  Kind of annoying when I only have one chant, but thats not the real problem.  
<br />

<br />
So I chant down the walrus and everythings great.  I then charm another, sick it on one and loop my swarm around to get on my pet...except it doesn't...  They continue to chase after me while my pet and the walrus I told him to attack duke it out in some kind of freaky blubber-battle royal. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" />  So I loop around again, and again, same result.  Then charm breaks and I get all pissed off.  
<br />

<br />
I'm pulling them only with proximity agro, and I'm only doing dmg to the one ex-pet the whole time.  So what I'm asking here is what am I doing wrong?</span></td>
