			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Problems with swarming<a name="32020"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 04 3:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have the same problem, especially when I was doing Spirocs.  I made a variety of changes that helped me some.  First, trying to make my second pet the mob my first pet was beating on helped some.  When chanting down, circle as far away from the mobs as possible.  It seems like a chant landing on a mob builds up a little aggro, and being farther away negates some of it.  Also, stand as far away as possible while your pet is being beaten on.  Just make sure to use a pet health key and not rely on the pet window health bar.  Don't pulse selo's while just standing there watching, either.  Each pulse can build up small amounts of aggro (the 49 selo's helped this a lot).  Same with other songs (especially hymn).  Finally, make sure your swarm is far away from you when you loot the dead ones.
<br />

<br />
I could be wrong on some of these, but I tried each one individually, and each seemed to help some.  I'm still having the problem, but I can usually get through 8-10 mobs before they all stick to me now.  If anyone else ha other suggestions, I'd love to hear them, too.
<br />

<br />
Nuinn</span></td>
