				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Problems with swarming<a name="32094"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 04 7:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a hot key that does a
<br />

<br />
/pet target
<br />
/assist
<br />
/pause 5
<br />
/pet target
<br />

<br />
This way I get the pet's target (regardless of which mob I told it to attack initially) into my toggle targets &quot;buffer&quot;.  As soon as charm breaks, and I chant the current pet to death, I can toggle targets to get to the new pet.
<br />

<br />
This reduces, but does not eliminate aggro build up over time.  For some mob types, you'll want to zone every once in a while to clean the hate list of all the mobs.  (Or use fading memories if you have it)
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
