			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Problems with swarming<a name="32356"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 1 04 3:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One factor that can affect your swarm is self buffing.  This is ok in AE kiting because who cares if you have more agro.  In swarming agro management is everything.
<br />

<br />
Some songs generate a lot of agro - Hymn of Restoration is one of those.  Also if you use selos it eventually will cause enough agro to cause the swarm not to stop at your pet.
<br />

<br />
Things you can do:
<br />

<br />
1) use sow potions or pulse selos only when draging the swarm
<br />
2) DON'T play self buffs - get regen items
<br />
3) Put a little extra distance between you and your swarm.
<br />

<br />
Hopefully this should fix it.
<br />

<br />
On a related note:  I have never had much luck managing my pets previous target and it has never mattered.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
