			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Problems with swarming<a name="32435"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 2 04 3:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The level 27 charm generates more agro than our later charm songs.  As such it is not ideal for swarm kiting because it generates a ton of agro from mobs who see you use it on one of their compatriots.  The ideal use for this song is to chain mezz a single mob against a single mob.  One on one fights, sometimes 2 on one fights.  Giants are great for this and you can charm most of the giants in the giant fort in EW, they make great pets.  I like to get a giant pet then drag him around killing anything that cons even or db, at least that's how I used the 27 charm.  I've found and heard from many other bards, that it just isn't condusive to swarming.
<br />

<br />
The 39 and 64 songs only grab signifigant agro from their actual targets so you can pretty easily manage agro, keeping it on your pet without resorting to the buffering thing.  Example, I'll grab a dozen or so mobs in PoN, as many as 15 sometimes, any more than that and your pet often dies before you can break charm.  I charm one, get it to 40% start invis and by the time invis finishes my pet is in the teens, chant it down then F8 for nearest target and charm that, F8 again, /pet attack hotkey, F1x2 to retarget pet, invis, chant, F8, charm, F8, /pet attack, F1, F1, invis, etc.
<br />

<br />
Basically, you're not ready to swarm kite yet.  Charm kite till your 39 then swarm to your hearts content.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
